import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['temperature'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of hourly temperature in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['temperature'], data['wind'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Temperature (°C)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between temperature and wind speed in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data['pressure'], vert=False, showmeans=True, meanline=True, whis=1.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Pressure (mb)')
    ax.axvline(data['pressure'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["pressure"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average hourly pressure in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    plt.ylabel('Frequency')

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temperature'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of temperature in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature (°C)')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
